<!-- vraag_01 -->
    <div id="vraag_01" style="position: absolute; transform: translate(-50%, -50%) translate3d(21000px, -1500px, 0px) rotateX(0deg) rotateY(0deg) rotateZ(0deg) scale(1); transform-style: preserve-3d; "  class="step slide past" data-x="21000" data-y="-1500">

     <div style="width: 90%;  position: absolute; top: 20px; text-align:center;"><p style="font-size:200%;">Vraag 1</p><p style="font-size:100%; position:relative; top:20px;"></p></div>

<div style="position: absolute; top: 200px; left:100px; text-align:left; font-size:100%;">

<p>When you start the X Window System, which series of programs and/or scripts would most closely describe
the start-up process?</p><br>
<ul>
<li style="list-style:disc;">xdm -> xinit -> xinitrc -> Xclients</li>
<li style="list-style:disc;">kde -> xinitrc -> xinit -> Xclients</li>
<li style="list-style:disc;">startx -> xinitrc -> Xclients -> kde</li>
<li style="list-style:disc;">startx -> xinit -> xinitrc -> Xclients</li>
<li style="list-style:disc;">startx -> xinit -> Xclients -> xinitrc</li>
</ul>


</div>

	<div id="container" style="position: absolute; bottom: 0; font-size:40%;">
  		<div id="left"><a href="http://www.linuxamsterdam.nl" target="_blank"><img src="la.svg" width=204px height=68px></a></div>
  		<div id="right"><a href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/" target="_blank"><img src="cc_by-sa.svg" width=88px height=31px></a></div>
