<!-- vraag_02 -->
    <div id="vraag_02" style="position: absolute; transform: translate(-50%, -50%) translate3d(22000px, -1500px, 0px) rotateX(0deg) rotateY(0deg) rotateZ(0deg) scale(1); transform-style: preserve-3d; "  class="step slide past" data-x="220000" data-y="-1500">

     <div style="width: 90%;  position: absolute; top: 20px; text-align:center;"><p style="font-size:200%;">Vraag 2</p><p style="font-size:100%; position:relative; top:20px;"></p></div>

<div style="position: absolute; top: 200px; left:100px; text-align:left; font-size:100%;">

<p>Why is the xhost program considered dangerous to use?</p><br>
<ul>
<li style="list-style:disc;">It makes it difficult to uniquely identify a computer on the network.</li>
<li style="list-style:disc;">It allows easy access to your X server by other users</li>
<li style="list-style:disc;">It logs sensitive information to syslog.</li>
<li style="list-style:disc;">It makes your computer share network resources without any authentication.</li>
<li style="list-style:disc;">It is a graphical DNS tool with known exploits.</li>
</ul>

</div>

